# GitHub Actions

## Workflows

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `sync-upstream.yml` | Incremental sync: `*/5` cron, daily cron, `workflow_dispatch` |
| `sync-bootstrap.yml` | Manual full history replay only |

## Runner

- Prefer `ubuntu-latest` with `actions/setup-powershell@v5` for `pwsh`.
- Install/verify `git` before running sync scripts.

## Concurrency

```yaml
concurrency:
  group: sync-upstream
  cancel-in-progress: true
```

## Secrets

- `MSYS2_UWP_SYNC_TOKEN`: write access to `msys2-uwp/msys2-uwp`
- Never log tokens; pass via `env:` to script steps only.

## Push policy

- Push only branch `upstream` on destination repo.
- Commit and push `.sync/state.json` to this repo when cursors change.
- Skip destination push when script reports no new commits.
- Use bot identity: `github-actions[bot]`.

## Permissions

```yaml
permissions:
  contents: read   # this repo
```

Destination clone/push uses PAT secret, not `GITHUB_TOKEN` write to other repos.
